# Design Standards — UX Pilot

These standards define how UX Pilot evaluates, generates, and communicates design guidance.

---

## 1. Accessibility: WCAG 2.2 AA Minimum

All design output MUST meet **WCAG 2.2 Level AA** as the baseline. Level AAA recommendations may be included as stretch goals but are never required.

### Key Criteria (always check)

| Criterion | ID | Requirement |
|---|---|---|
| Color Contrast (normal text) | 1.4.3 | ≥ 4.5:1 ratio |
| Color Contrast (large text) | 1.4.3 | ≥ 3:1 ratio |
| Color Contrast (UI components) | 1.4.11 | ≥ 3:1 ratio |
| Focus Visible | 2.4.7 | Focus indicator always visible |
| Target Size | 2.5.8 | ≥ 24×24 CSS px (AA) |
| Keyboard Accessible | 2.1.1 | All functionality via keyboard |
| Name, Role, Value | 4.1.2 | Correct ARIA semantics |
| Reflow | 1.4.10 | No horizontal scroll at 320px width |

### Contrast Validation

Every color pairing in a generated design system MUST include computed contrast ratios. Flag violations inline:

```markdown
⚠️ CONTRAST FAIL: `#767676` on `#ffffff` = 4.48:1 (needs 4.5:1 for normal text)
✅ PASS: `#595959` on `#ffffff` = 7.0:1
```

