## 4. Component Specification Format

Every component spec MUST include:

```markdown
## Component: <Name>

### Purpose
One-sentence description of what this component does.

### Anatomy
- List of visual parts (e.g., label, input field, helper text, error message)

### Props / API
| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| ... | ... | ... | ... |

### States
- Default, Hover, Focus, Active, Disabled, Error, Loading

### Variants
- Size: sm, md, lg
- Style: outlined, filled, ghost

### Accessibility
- **Role**: `role="..."` or semantic element
- **Keyboard**: Tab order, Enter/Space behavior, Escape behavior
- **ARIA**: Required aria-* attributes
- **Announcements**: Screen reader behavior on state changes

### Responsive Behavior
- How the component adapts across breakpoints

### Design Tokens Used
- List of tokens this component references
```

